                        <note n="8" xml:id="note-t-8">
                            

<p>In a letter written to Theo on 24 December 1873, <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_526">Mr van Gogh</rs> quoted one of Vincent’s letters from London: ‘Vincent writes that he really enjoys so many good things, more all the time – and then he says</p>

<p>“the valuable life,</p>

<p>your gift, O God!”’ (FR b2675).</p>

<p>The quotation was taken from the poem ‘Een kruis met rozen’ (A cross with roses) by <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_615">P.A. de Génestet</rs>. See De Génestet 1869, vol. 2, p. 208.</p>
